macro.title: 15% of Home Purchases Fell Through in October, Up Slightly From a Year Earlier
macro.what: Homebuyers are getting cold feet due to high housing costs and economic uncertainty
macro.why: Inventory and velocity drive pricing power and volume.
macro.market: Rising inventory/DOM tilts to buyers; tight supply supports prices.

macro.title: Realtor.com predicts gradual housing market recovery in 2026
macro.what: Recovery is expected to remain slow, with existing-home sales well below normal levels amid broader political and economic uncertainty.
macro.why: Relevant development for housing and markets.
macro.market: Watch second-order effects across builders, lenders, and REITs.

macro.title: Redfin Economists’ Weekly Take: Mortgage Rates May Bounce Around Ahead of Fed Meeting
macro.what: This Week In A Nutshell Rates fell last week as financial markets increasingly priced in a rate cut at next Wednesday’s Fed meeting, but an absence of recent jobs and inflation data makes this one particularly difficult to predict
macro.why: Rates & inflation shape discount rates and housing affordability.
macro.market: Lower rates support demand/valuations; higher rates pressure builders/REITs and slow transactions.
